data.title: Blues beaten by Tasmania in Hobart Shield match
data.meta_description: NSW have been defeated by an innings and one run in their Sheffield Shield fixture against Tasmania…
data.text:
Tasmania’s first-innings lead proved insurmountable to overcome, despite a courageous unbeaten second-innings showing from Chris Green (61*).

Ollie Davies was the leading run-scorer for the Blues in both innings, registering knocks of 67 and 62 off the back of an inaugural First-Class century in the team's recent 10-wicket victory against WA.

View the full match report from cricket.com.au – HERE

See the full match scorecard – HERE

The Blues return to the SCG for their next Sheffield Shield outing, where they’ll face off against Tasmania again. This match is scheduled to commence on Tuesday, November 28.
